SIMPLE: mouthpiece
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mouthpiece
<hw>Mouth"piece`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
part of a musical or other instrument to which the mouth is applied in
using it; <as>as, the <ex>mouthpiece</ex> of a bugle, or of a tobacco
pipe</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An appendage to an inlet or outlet opening of a pipe
or vessel, to direct or facilitate the inflow or outflow of a
fluid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who delivers the opinion of others or of
another; a spokesman; <as>as, the <ex>mouthpiece</ex> of his
party</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Egmont was imprudent enough to make himself the
<qex>mouthpiece</qex> of their remonstrance.</q>
<rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>A person's lawyer.</def>
<mark>[slang]</mark> <note>This is a term that was used sometimes in old
movies. When a tough bad guy was arrested he might say ⟦ldquo⟧I ain't
sayin' nothin' without my <ex>mouthpiece</ex>!⟦rdquo⟧</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mouthwash</ent>⟦br⟧
